  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\n2.19.1\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\nThe go-ethereum team switched to using `input` instead of `data` in their transaction objects in `ethclient`. This caused our `eth_call`s to break since hardhat does not expect `input`. Ideally hardhat node can support both fields.\r\n\r\nHardhat node will instead just set the data field to `0x` which will cause most `eth_call`s to revert with error `Transaction reverted without a reason string`\r\n\r\nTheir PR: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/28078\r\n\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\nMake a transaction where the data payload is using field `input` instead of `data`. \r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\n_No response_",
